<title>UK: RESEARCH ALERT - Salomon picks stocks for 1997.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - Salomon picks stocks for 1997.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Salomon Brothers on Tuesday named 18 European stocks it expects to outperform during 1997, as part of its 119-strong list of &quot;Top Global Stock Picks&quot; for the year ahead.</p>
<p>In the UK, Salomon's preferred stocks are building materials group BPB Industries Plc, British Petroleum Co Plc, banking group Barclays Plc, insurer Royal Sun Alliance and media group Carlton Communications Plc.  </p>
<p>Other European stocks on Salomon's list were Dutch chemicals group Akzo Nobel, Irish paper and packaging group Jefferson Smurfit, Spanish steelmaker Acerinox, Germany's Volkswagen, French oil group Elf Aquitaine, Russian oil and gas groups Purneftegas and Surgutneftegaz, Italian telecoms group STET, Polish paintmaker Polifarb Ciesyn, Russian utility Mosenergro, Zurich Insurance, Spanish bank Banco Santander and France's Credit National.  </p>
<p>&quot;This comprehensive report, significantly expanded from last year's, combines into one volume the collective wisdom and insight of Salomon Brothers' analysts, equity strategists and economists worldwide,&quot; said Stephen Weiss, Salomon's global and U.S. equity research product manager.</p>
<p>&quot;I know of no other document like it on Wall Street.&quot;</p>
<p>-- David Holmes, London Newsroom +44 171 542 5106</p>
